00:30.000 --> 00:31.627
'T. S. Eliot said that

00:31.667 --> 00:36.343
'the purpose of literature
was to turn blood into ink.

00:36.375 --> 00:38.628
'Well, I tried that.

00:38.667 --> 00:42.297
'I published five collections
of poetry in eight years

00:42.333 --> 00:45.587
'and I bled like a hemophiliac.

00:45.625 --> 00:49.835
'Then, somewhere along the way,
the blood finally clotted.

00:50.083 --> 00:54.168
'Over time,
the scab became a scar

00:54.208 --> 00:57.883
'and now I can scarcely
feel the wound.

00:58.125 --> 01:01.709
'All the arteries and veins
are dried out.

01:01.750 --> 01:05.209
'I no longer turn blood
into ink.

01:05.250 --> 01:09.710
'These days, I turn whiskey
into journalism.

01:09.750 --> 01:12.629
'I haven't written a poem
since 1987.'

